rest_of_day_open: I am hoping to get myself to get outside every day to exercise. So far I have not had as much success with that as I would like. But when I was out yesterday it was easier than it has been, so I am going to try to focus on that as a way to help me motivate myself. Other than that, I am staying home to keep from spreading infection. I am hoping that I do get together with my ex-wife. When we saw each other for a few minutes, she said she would like to see me again soon. I was just picking p an item from my son's car but we talked for a bit. It was very nice to see her. Nice to see anyone in person.
critical_positive: At this moment, I wish I had bothered to say his name to him several times. I am out of practice meeting new people. That helps me remember the name. I do not remember his name. What worked really well is he asked me a lot of questions, directing the conversation to what he wanted to hear. I did the same, it was how I initially engaged him. We also just went with it organically to quite an extent. Both of these worked in favor of it.
critical_negative: He seemed a bit shy. Which is why I asked a lot of questions initially. He is very young, which tends to make it so we have less in common. Yet he seemed interested in the things I said that are indicators of my age. My children. A friend died a couple years back. Something we talked about my experience is 30 years old.
employ_7_TEXT: disabled but I was working part time to supplement social security until April 8 when I read that hypertension makes me more likely to get sick from covid19 and more likely to have permanent damage or even die. My employer terminated my employment June 10. I am receiving unemployment benefits, but will not go back to work until it is safe to do so. I have not done gig work since March, but I could start immediately with that and look for a new part time job. I would start with my old employer.
